title: For Sale:  Headshot Tactical Customs-Clarification on the hate postings on me
postcontent:
To anyone who knows me, and all the loyal customs that have notified me of the 2 hate postings on armslist, I appreciate you taking the time and effort to give me support and state that you don't agree with those listings, it means a lot to me to know that people who have been to my shop and know me agree that those postings are false. I found out the poster has never been here before, has never spoken to me, and have no idea why he is mad enough to start ranting about me. Here are some facts-
I am a premium armslist vendor-this means I pay $200 a year to post ads here and armslist.com has a copy of my FFL on file and verified my shop so I'm a legitimate dealer. I paid this fee because it lets me post as many ads as I want and lets everyone looking know immediately that they won't get scammed and if they send me money I'm going to send them the correct item they paid for. 
I'm sorry I list a lot of guns on this site. I always pick the Dealer listings so people can easily skip over my ads by clicking the Private Party button. I thought by carrying a ton of guns, ammo, and accessories I was doing a good thing for all of us. I figure most people come here looking for guns, ammo, and accessories and the more I carry the better chance I have to stock something that someone wants. Does anyone think too many guns is a bad thing?

I'm a small dealer that runs my shop out of the garage next to my house. I paid big money to get the zoning changed to commercial, and get my FFL license, and take the risk of having everyone on the internet know where I live and approximately what I stock at my home. Take a look at the 12 or 13 pages of what I have listed up here for sale, and think that I still have a lot more than that here for sale. I mainly list guns, a few mags, and ammo on armslist but until you set foot in my shop you have no clue how much inventory I keep in stock. Everything from  hard to get parts, magazines, targets, lasers, lights, holsters, cleaning kits, night sights, triggers, stocks, grips, cases, range bags, and on and on that I paid for up front to have ready and available for anyone who makes the effort to come here. One guy in his garage that has everything from $250 revolvers to Springfield M1A Super Match rifles. I try to always keep the cool stuff that not many shops have in stock. SRM M1216 16-shot 12 gauge? I have 2 of those. Kel-Tec KSG's-2 of those two. You want an AR pistol but want something different? I'll usually build one for you while you wait. Think about How many other gun dealers can you call or text directly at almost any hour of the day or night? How many people online give a complete stranger their address and say come on over? All my prices are based off of what I paid and I generally am so broke I sell them at $20 over dealer cost for anyone willing to spend their cash here, I'm always willing to work with anybody. If I have a hard to get gun for sale at $1200, it's because I paid $1100 or more for it-but at least I have it here. 
I jump to take care of my customers. I've worked all night to get duty guns running for a LE officer that had to qualify the next day. I've ordered $3500 guns for people using my own money that never showed to pick them up-I'm not happy about it when it happens but it's the way things work and I move on. 
My shop lives and dies by word of mouth and it physically made me sick to see hate postings by someone I've never wronged or had dealings with and has no idea about me or how I am in the shop. If anyone has a problem with me selling too many guns on a website that is made for buying and selling guns please feel free to contact me directly and voice your opinion instead of just posting a rant up here that ruins my night. 
If you made it this far, I thank you for taking the time to hear me out. If you have any questions about me, feel free to call or text me at REDACTED or reply on here. I may take awhile if I'm busy but I'll get back to you. 

If you're that middle aged guy sitting in your mothers basement where you live randomly talking trash online, I hope you stub your toe really hard on momma's coffee table and it hurts for a good 5 minutes and you reflect on why you're such a jerk.
